.SH DESCRIPTION
Vector SIL Kit Adapter veIPC connects a veIPC TCP socket server
to a SIL Kit simulation.
The first positional argument is mandatory and must be of the form
\fI<host>:<port>,<toAdapterTopic>,<fromAdapterTopic>\fR.
SIL Kit-specific CLI arguments can be overwritten by the configuration
file passed via \fB--configuration\fR.
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "<host>:<port>,<toAdapterTopic>,<fromAdapterTopic>"
Mandatory positional argument. Describes the veIPC TCP server endpoint
and the topic names used for communication between the adapter and SIL Kit.
.IP "--configuration <path>"
Path to the .silkit.yaml or .json configuration file.
.IP "--name <participant's name>"
Set the participant's name. Defaults to 'SilKitAdapterVeIpc'.
.IP "--registry-uri silkit://<host>:<port>"
The silkit:// URI the adapter should connect to. Defaults to 'silkit://localhost:8501'.
.IP "--log <level>"
Log to stdout with level 'Trace', 'Debug', 'Warn', 'Info', 'Error', 'Critical', or 'Off'. Defaults to 'Info'.
.IP "--endianness <mode>"
Set the endianness used by the veIPC communication. Valid values are 'big_endian' and 'little_endian'. Defaults to 'little_endian'.
.PP
Example:
.PP
.nf
sil-kit-adapter-veipc localhost:6666,toSocket,fromSocket --endianness little_endian
.fi
.PP
Pass \fB--version\fR to print the adapter version.
